# Flag-validation contract for `agents try`. None of these commands
# hit the network — they all fail in BuildMessages /
# NormalizeCompatibility / cobra mutually-exclusive checks before
# client construction.
#
# Ungated: runs whenever the standard e2e env is present.

# `agents try` requires --config
! exec algolia agents try -m hi
stderr 'required flag\(s\) "config"'

# `agents try` requires one of --input or --message
! exec algolia agents try -c cfg.json
stderr 'one of --input or --message is required'

# `agents try` rejects --input and --message together (cobra
# mutually-exclusive guard, fires before our handler)
! exec algolia agents try -c cfg.json -i msg.json -m hi
stderr '\[input message\]'

# `agents try` rejects an invalid --compatibility value
! exec algolia agents try -c cfg.json -m hi --compatibility v9
stderr 'invalid --compatibility'

-- cfg.json --
{"model":"gpt-4o-mini","instructions":"e2e"}

-- msg.json --
[{"role":"user","content":"hi"}]
